## Encoder-Control + Preset Storage Migration Plan (Daisy Delay)

  ### Summary

  Replace analog pot-driven parameter control with encoder-driven editing, add 8 persistent local presets in QSPI
  flash, and document the new hardware/UI workflow.
  Chosen defaults: 4 encoders + shift, onboard QSPI, tap=load / hold=save, chorded preset mode, preset stores mode
  + 7 params, 8 slots.

  ### Implementation Changes

  - Control model refactor
      - Replace pot sampling path with encoder delta path in Controls/ControlState.
      - Introduce ParamEditState (normalized [0..1] values for all 7 params) as the single control source for
        BuildParams.
      - Keep MIDI CC override behavior, but apply CC updates into ParamEditState (so OLED and saved presets always
        reflect effective values).
  - Encoder mapping and interaction
      - Hardware target: keep current mode encoder and add 4 encoder pots for parameters.
      - Encoder parameter map:
          - Primary layer: Time, Repeats, Mix, Filter
          - Shift layer (mode-encoder switch held): Grit, ModSpd, ModDep, unused/reserved
      - Mode encoder turn continues to select delay mode exactly as today.
      - Encoder acceleration and step scaling:
          - base step 0.005 normalized/tick
          - fast-turn step 0.015 when consecutive ticks arrive within 40 ms
          - clamp hard to [0,1].
  - Preset subsystem
      - Add PresetManager using daisy::PersistentStorage (QSPI backend).
      - New persisted schema (versioned):
          - header: magic, version, CRC, active slot
          - 8 slots, each with: valid, DelayModeId mode, float norm[7]
      - Boot behavior:
          - load storage; if invalid/empty, initialize slot 0 from defaults and mark valid.
          - recall active slot into ParamEditState and mode.
      - Runtime behavior:
          - preset load copies slot values to ParamEditState, activates stored mode, updates audio immediately.
          - preset save writes current mode + normalized params to selected slot and commits only on data change.
  - Preset UI/footswitch behavior (no tap-tempo regression)
      - Normal tap switch behavior remains tap tempo.
      - Preset actions are only active while mode-encoder switch is held:
          - tap short: load current preset slot
          - tap long (>=700 ms): save to current preset slot (with overwrite confirmation banner on OLED)
      - Slot selection while holding mode-encoder switch:
          - turn mode encoder to select slot 1..8 (wrap).
  - Display/documentation updates
      - Extend OLED rendering with lightweight status row: active slot, shift-layer indicator, save/load feedback.
      - Update README hardware section for encoder-pot wiring and new pin map.
      - Add README “Preset Workflow” and “Encoder Layer Map” sections.
      - Update architecture notes: control flow becomes Encoders/MIDI -> ParamEditState -> ParamSet.
      - Add a short migration note: old pot hardware is unsupported after this change.

  ### Public Interfaces / Types to Add or Change

  - ControlState: remove pot_normalized[NUM_POTS]; add encoder delta fields (mode + 4 param encoders) and modifier/
    hold flags.
  - constants.h:
      - rename conceptual NUM_POTS usage to NUM_PARAMS (value remains 7).
      - add preset constants: PRESET_SLOT_COUNT=8, PRESET_HOLD_MS=700, step/accel constants.
  - New module: src/presets/preset_manager.h/.cpp with:
      - Init(), LoadActive(...), LoadSlot(slot, ...), SaveSlot(slot, ...), SetActiveSlot(slot), GetActiveSlot().
  - DisplayManager::Update(...) gains minimal preset UI state input (active slot + transient status flags).

  ### Test Plan

  - Unit-level (host/logic)
      - encoder step/accel math and clamping.
      - preset serialization/deserialization, version mismatch fallback, CRC reject path.
      - slot bounds/wrap (0..7) and save-on-dirty behavior.
  - Firmware integration
      - boot with empty QSPI: defaults created, slot 1 recalled.
      - save slot, power-cycle, reload confirms persistence.
      - preset recall updates both mode and audible parameter state in one control cycle.
      - MIDI CC after recall updates value and subsequent save persists updated state.
  - Manual hardware acceptance
      - all 7 params reachable via primary+shift layer.
      - tap tempo works normally when mode-encoder switch is not held.
      - held-mode + tap short loads slot; held-mode + tap long saves slot.
      - OLED shows slot and action feedback; no blocking/audio glitches during save.

  ### Assumptions and Defaults

  - Existing mode encoder remains in hardware; 4 additional encoder pots are added for parameter editing.
  - QSPI is available and safe for infrequent preset writes (save-only on explicit long-hold).
  - Preset format v1 stores only mode + 7 normalized params (not bypass state, MIDI learn map, or tap tempo
    history).
  - MIDI Program Change behavior remains mode-select only (not mapped to local preset slots) in this iteration.
